                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#100v">Fol. 100v</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 100v: ተስፋ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘወ[ሀ]ቦ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ …</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is very crudely written beneath Additio 1 and repeated on fol. 101v. It states that Täsfa Mikaʾel donated the Ms. to the church of St. Michael. Other persons, such as Wälättä Ṣadǝqan, are also mentioned.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Erased notes in the bottom margin of fol. 52vb.&#xD;
- Erased notes on fol. 87rb, partly overwritten with a short supplication for the “maids” Fǝqǝrtä Täklä Haymanot and ʿƎśśetä Haymanot, in red. &#xD;
- Tämälläs-signs indicating the place where the omissions, written in the margins (fols. 3ra, 3vb, 6va, 8rb, 10ra, 20rb, 23vb, 28va, 32ra, 35rb, 35vb, 36rb, 37vb, 42rb, 44ra, 46ra, 48vb, 49rb, 49va, 56rb, 64ra, 65vb, 66va, 69va, 70rb, 74rb), belong.&#xD;
- Many corrections written in a secondary hand over erasures: e.g., fols. 2rb, 2va, 3vb-5rb, 6va (several lines), 9va, 10ra-11va, 17ra, 20rb, 23va, 27v, 34vb, 37r, 45r, 46va, 49vb-50va, 51v, 52vb (incipit of a section), 53rb, 55vb (incipit of a section), 66va-68rb, 75r, 78rb (incipit of a section), 86ra. &#xD;
- Erasures are marked with thin lines: e.g., fols. 3rb, 4ra, 4vb, 10rb, 20rb, 24rb, 41va, 66ra.&#xD;
- Erasures without marking: e.g., fols.6ra, 22va, 50vb, 66ra.&#xD;
- Omitted letters and words sometimes inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 7rb, 25vb, 27va, 50ra, 68rb, 75rb, 76va, 80rb, 86rb.</item>
